cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.DC, cs.NE, cs.AR 

This paper is likely to belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category as it discusses low precision training strategies for deep models. It also involves testing the ResNet50 model on the ImageNet-full dataset, which is a common benchmark for machine learning models. 

It could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as the ResNet50 model is commonly used for image classification tasks. 

The paper also discusses communication cost reduction and model compression, which are relevant to the cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) sub-category. 

The use of low precision training for neural networks is also relevant to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category. 

Finally, the paper proposes a solution for IEEE FP-16 format throughout the training process, which could be relevant to the cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) sub-category as it involves hardware implementation of deep learning models.
